name: Los Angeles Mission
review_text: Love this place. The mission is a beacon of hope in a rough part of skid row. If you honestly need help they are here to serve you. The staff are men and women serving Christ through the mission. I have been here about 12 months in the rehabilitation program and love it. Next month I graduate the program. They have helped me with so much. From a safe clean place to lay my head at night, clean clothes every day, showers and hygiene products, education, one on one and group counseling, and so much more. This place is a refuge for the lost and broken. I cant thank God enough for his provision in this rough season in my life. Currently they are helping me with finding employment and more permanent housing.  If you are honest and need a another chance at life the mission is here. Love to my chaplains and the staff.

name: Los Angeles Mission
review_text: LA Mission is a Homeless shelter.....It serves emergency needs on a first come first served basis. The in need is for example: barefoot, extremely grimy, a guy who has no place to sleep at night or a lady that needs a  blanket. I have seen operation staff and at times students help people with clothes, food, showers, blankets and a bed. And yes they have a schedule to keep because the program students have other duties besides staffing the homeless shelter in every department that comes in contact with people in need. It is not perfect but everyday tries to live up to the frase "What would Jesus do?"
